{"word":"θροέω","slug":"θροέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θροέω</b></el> <el>(θροέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θρόος'><el>θρόος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to cry aloud</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:— <i>to speak, say, utter</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>;—and in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to tell out, declare</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be troubled</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}